# ASCII Art Generator

Generate beautiful ASCII art from text using multiple libraries: pyfiglet, cowsay, boxes, and image-to-ascii conversion.

## Features

- **Text-to-ASCII** with pyfiglet (large fonts, banner-style)
- **Character art** with cowsay (speech bubbles, ASCII characters)
- **Boxed text** with boxes library (borders, shadows, colors)
- **Image-to-ASCII** conversion (convert images to text art)
- **Multiple font styles** (banner, slant, shadow, etc.)
- **Color support** (ANSI colors for terminal display)

## Installation

```bash
# Install all ASCII art tools at once
pip install pyfiglet cowsay boxes image-to-ascii
```

## Usage

### 1. Text-to-ASCII (pyfiglet)

```bash
# Basic banner
figlet "Hello World"

# Large font
figlet -f big "HELLO"

# Multiple fonts
figlet -f banner -f slant -f shadow "MAGIC"

# Save to file
figlet "Awesome" > ascii.txt
```

### 2. Character Art (cowsay)

```bash
# Default cow
cowsay "Hello, Hermes!"

# Custom cow
cowsay -f dragon "AI Agent"
cowsay -f skeleton "Code Review"
cowsay -f tux "Linux Server"

# Twisted speech
cowsay -t "Surprise!"

# Eyes and tongue
cowsay -e oo -T U "Excited!"

# Save to file
cowsay "Save this" > cowsay.txt
```

### 3. Boxed Text (boxes)

```bash
# Simple box
echo "Hello World" | boxes -d cat

# Fancy box
echo "Hermes Agent" | boxes -d dog | boxes -a c

# Custom dimensions
echo "Banner" | boxes -d bubble -s 50x10

# Colored box
echo "Color" | boxes -d shadow | boxes -c cyan

# Save to file
echo "Content" | boxes -d bubble > boxed.txt
```

### 4. Image-to-ASCII (image-to-ascii)

```bash
# Convert image to ASCII
image-to-ascii image.jpg

# Custom font size
image-to-ascii --font-size 20 image.png

# Color mode (requires imagemagick)
image-to-ascii --color image.jpg

# Thresholding (grayscale only)
image-to-ascii --threshold 128 image.png

# Save to file
image-to-ascii image.jpg > ascii_art.txt

# High resolution
image-to-ascii --font-size 30 --width 200 image.png > hi-res.txt
```

